messages.message: Has anyone else experienced a lot of kernel panics on their work computer before (especially with the dev setup)?

When I first got here, I inherited Warren’s old computer, and it was doing it about every other hour (even with a complete wipe), so @sam (bless her soul) replaced it with a new one, which worked great
However, now it’s starting again on my new computer due to watchdog (hardware timer) timeouts from watchdogd
Initially it was once a week which was frustrating but ok, and I just had my second one of the day which is not as ok. Here’s the error report:
